cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.DS

The paper deals with learning a dictionary for thresholded features, which is a common task in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves theoretical guarantees and optimization algorithms, which suggest that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper uses synthetic and real data, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
